<HEADER>
A6023 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w BC-SAFE-TIPS14-COX     08-13 0328
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SAFE-TIPS14-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With SAFE-SCHOOLS.
 &HT;    Graphics editors: Covers of the booklets are available as PDF
files at the listed web page.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FREE BOOKLETS ON SCHOOL SAFETY
</P>
<P>
   A free single copy of any of the following booklets on school
safety is available by calling a toll-free number, 1-800-USA-LEARN,
or downloading from the U.S. Department of Education's Web site
(http://www.ed.gov/offices/OESE/SDFS/safeschools.html).
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Early Warning, Timely Response, A Guide to Safe Schools.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Preventing Youth Hate Crime, A Manual for Schools and
Communities.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Protecting Students from Harassment and Hate Crime, A Guide
for Schools.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Preventing Bullying, A Manual for Schools and Communities.''
</P>
<P>
   SIGNS OF A SAFE SCHOOL
</P>
<P>
   A panel of experts assembled by the Department of Education
compiled this list of signs of a safe school:
</P>
<P>
   _ Supervises access to the building and grounds.
</P>
<P>
   _ Reduces class size and school size.
</P>
<P>
   _ Adjusts schedules and hallway traffic patterns to limit
potential for conflicts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Conducts a building safety audit with help from police and
school security experts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Closes school campus during lunch periods.
</P>
<P>
   _ Adopts a policy on school uniforms.
</P>
<P>
   _ Supervises hallways and other areas where incidents are
likely.
</P>
<P>
   _ Supervises at key times when children are outside classrooms.
</P>
<P>
   _ Has adults, including visiting parents, throughout the
building.
</P>
<P>
   _ Staggers dismissal times and lunch periods.
</P>
<P>
   _ Monitors grounds, including landscaping, parking lots and bus
stops.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coordinates with police on routes kids walk or ride to school.
</P>
<P>
   _ Identifies safe areas for staff and children to go in a
crisis.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lacks buildings that are dirty, despoiled by graffiti, too
cold or too hot, unsanitary or in need of repair.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
