<TEXT>
<P>
   These business stories for release Saturday, August 14, 1999,
are moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the financial (f) category. Stories also
moving in lifestyle will be marked with (f, l).
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   WOMEN-TVCHANNEL _ Turner Broadcasting has postponed the launch
of its Women's Channel, concerned that the cost was too high as the
company prepares to launch two other channels next year. The
Atlanta-based cable TV programmer said, ``We are putting
development of the network on hold.'' (Haddad, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in the (l) Lifestyle and (f) Financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   UPS-TAXES _ United Parcel Service lost a significant battle in
tax court, but the war is not over yet. A look at company's options
and question of what impact this will have on its planned stock
offering, which the company says will go ahead. (McNaughton,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BRONNER-HAIRSHOW _ ATLANTA _ A preview of the Bronner Brothers
hair show, which kicks off Saturday and is expected to attract at
least 75,000 people to Atlanta. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   CABLE-INTERNET-HACKER _ Time Warner touts its cable modem
Internet service as the best thing since sliced bread. But some
customers say it comes with a problem: Security. (Gallaga, Austin
Amnerican-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TECHNO-FILE _ Over the last few weeks a war has been waged
between AOL and Microsoft over open access to instant messaging,
the technology that lets users shoot private messages directly to
other users that pop up on their screen. Instant Messaging may not
seem like a big deal, but the big companies are clashing for a
reason _ IM is merely a preview of things to come. (Gallaga, Austin
Amnerican-Statesman).
</P>
