 &HT;    LABASTIDA BIO BOX
 &HT;    With MEXICO-LABASTIDA-$ADV14.
 &HT;    For Use Sat., Aug. 14 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By SUSAN FERRISS 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRANCISCO LABASTIDA OCHOA
</P>
<P>
   AGE: 57
</P>
<P>
   TRAINING: Studied economics at Mexico's National Autonomous
University (UNAM). Also taught at the UNAM.
</P>
<P>
   ELECTED OFFICE: Elected governor of the Pacific coast state of
Sinaloa, serving from 1987 to 1992.
</P>
<P>
   APPOINTMENTS: Named agriculture secretary in 1995 and then
interior minister in 1998 by President Ernesto Zedillo. Resigned
recently to run in the presidential primary of the Revolutionary
Institutional Party (PRI).
</P>
<P>
   Also served as head of Mexico's government toll roads agency;
ambassador to Portugal in the mid-1990s; secretary of energy and
state-run industries in the late 1980s; under-secretary of budget
and planning in the early 1980s.
</P>
