<P>
   RUSSIA-DAGESTAN (Moscow) _ As fighting continued in southern
Russia, the new prime minister threatens to launch air strikes
against Islamic militants in the breakaway republic of Chechnya,
risking a widening of the seven-day-old conflict in a neighboring
region, Dagestan. By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   With map. (MOVED)
