</P>
<P>
   LA-SHOOTING-MENTAL (Seattle) _ The mental health system in
Washington state got a clear and extensive look at Buford Furrow in
the months before he is alleged to have opened fire on school
children in a Jewish Community Center and killed a postal worker in
Los Angeles. What the mental health experts saw was a man who twice
slashed his arms so deep they required stitches, drank alcohol
until he blacked out, and espoused a deep hatred for anyone who is
not white. Yet, despite lengthy evaluations at mental institutions
here, and no shortage of resources, Furrow was never ordered to
remain under state psychiatric care. Instead, after serving nearly
six months for attempting to stab two hospital attendants, he was
released to normal parole supervision and required to take
medication designed to control psychotic impulses. By Timothy Egan.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-TEACH (Jerusalem) _ When the school year starts in a few
weeks Israeli textbooks, for the first time, will give the
Palestinian view of Israel's origin and will also for the first
time high schools will not teach history of Jews as completely
separate from history of other people. By Ethan Bronner. 1,900
words.
</P>
