   With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   GAYS-MILITARY (Washington) _ The Pentagon announces its first
major revision of guidelines for enforcement of its ``don't ask,
don't tell'' policy, but fails to satisfy gay rights advocates who
say that entrenched hostility toward homosexuals in uniform
continues to result in violent harassment, including last month's
brutal murder of a Army private in Kentucky. By Philip Shenon.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-GRAF-RETIRE (Undated) _ Germany's Steffi Graf, the
iconoclastic tennis dynamo whose perfectionist strivings and sonic
forehands carried her to 107 singles titles as well as a virtual
monopoly of the number one ranking at the extended peak of her
17-year career, announces her retirement in Heidelberg. Echoing
statements she made this year at the French Open and Wimbledon,
where she disclosed that her 1999 campaigns would be her last ever
at those slams, Graf, who in 1988 became the only player in history
to capture all four Grand Slam plus the Olympic gold medal,
confirmed that her nonpareil career was over, effective
immediately. By Robin Finn.
</P>
