<SLUG> BC-KODKIAN-HOLMER-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CARLSBAD SLAYING CASE SPURS REVIEW OF 1996 MURDER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By YVONNE ABRAHAM  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  BOSTON -- Police said Thursday they will ``take another
look'' at Raffi Kodikian, accused of killing his best friend in New
Mexico, in connection with the 1996 murder of Swedish nanny Karina
Holmer, whose torso was discovered in a dumpster behind a Fenway
building where Kodikian lived.
</P>
<P>
   Like many other potential witnesses, Kodikian, 25, was
interviewed by police seeking clues in Holmer's strangulation and
dismemberment.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody who lived in that building was questioned as part of
a routine canvass,'' said Detective Sergeant Margot Hill, a police
spokeswoman. ``That doesn't mean one way or another that any
suspicions were raised about him.''
</P>
<P>
   But Hill said the department would ``take another look'' at
Kodikian in light of the murder charge he faces. Kodikian told New
Mexico authorities he stabbed David Coughlin, 26, twice in the
heart to put a friend dying of thirst out of his misery.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll do it at the discretion of New Mexico police,'' she
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
