</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MADRAZO-BOX-$ADV15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MADRAZO BIO BOX
 &HT;    With MEXICO-MADRAZO-$ADV15.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., Aug. 15 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By SUSAN FERRISS 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ROBERTO MADRAZO PINTADO
</P>
<P>
   AGE: 48
</P>
<P>
   TRAINING: Studied law at Mexico's National Autonomous
University. Studied urban planning for one year at the University
of California at Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   ELECTED OFFICE: Elected senator from the Gulf coast state of
Tabasco in 1988. Elected federal deputy from Tabasco in 1991.
Elected governor of Tabasco in 1994, stepping down in July to run
for the presidential nomination for the Revolutionary Institutional
Party, PRI.
</P>
<P>
   APPOINTMENTS AND PARTY OFFICES: PRI youth leader in the 1970s;
presidential campaign coordinator for central Mexico in 1987;
president of the PRI's central committee in Tabasco in 1993.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
