<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Gingrich aide to be queried in divorce
 &HT;    By Francis X. Gilpin
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ A lawyer for the estranged wife of Newt Gingrich has
been given approval in the couple's divorce case to question a
congressional aide about her relationship with the former U.S.
House speaker.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta lawyer John C. Mayoue, who represents Marianne Gingrich,
said Friday he expects to be able to put Callista L. Bisek under
oath in Virginia in a few weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Bisek, 33, who lives outside of Washington, couldn't be reached
Friday at her Arlington, Va., home or on the job at the House
Agriculture Committee.
</P>
<P>
   Gingrich filed for divorce from Marianne Gingrich, his second
wife, on July 29 in Cobb County Superior Court.
</P>
<P>
   The Republican said in his petition to the court that the
marriage of 18 years was irretrievably broken.
</P>
<P>
   The couple separated May 10, according to Gingrich's petition.
</P>
<P>
   Mayoue, in his request to question Bisek, said ``this action is
a divorce case'' and Newt Gingrich's ``relationship with Callista
Bisek is in question.''
</P>
<P>
   Superior Court Judge Dorothy A. Robinson issued an order late
Thursday granting permission to Mayoue to set up a videotaped
deposition of Bisek.
</P>
<P>
   Mayoue said he intends to question Bisek about all aspects of
her relationship with Gingrich, who resigned his House seat after
1998 GOP election losses.
</P>
<P>
   The New York Daily News quoted unidentified sources Friday as
saying Gingrich and Bisek were seen around her home in the wee
hours last year.
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, he pushed for President Clinton's impeachment
in the Monica Lewinsky affair.
</P>
<P>
   Gingrich's lawyer, J. Randolph Evans of Atlanta, lamented the
turn that the divorce litigation has taken.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think it's very helpful when you're getting into
saber-rattling, which is what this is, because then it gets very
hurtful and very expensive for everybody concerned,'' Evans said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Evans said Mayoue requested and obtained permission to question
Bisek without giving him a chance to argue against it in court.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's fine. Everybody has their own style,'' said Evans.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're trying to keep the proceedings focused on what
proceedings like this should be focused on. That's reaching a fair
and equitable settlement for Marianne and Newt.''
</P>
<P>
   Gingrich's first marriage to the former Jackie Battley ended in
divorce and he wed his current wife within months of the final
dissolution.
</P>
<P>
   Jackie Gingrich has claimed Newt Gingrich first talked about
divorcing her while she recovered from cancer surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Newt Gingrich has disputed that.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
