Deborah Sullivan. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SHOOTING-HOPE (Los Angeles) _ Members of the North Valley Jewish
Community Center, families of the children who attend camp there
and their neighbors return to the Granada Hills facility tonight
for a ``hope and healing service'' in the wake of the shooting
rampage there Tuesday that left three camp kids, a 16-year-old
counselor and receptionist injured. By Dominic Berbeo. (Will move
in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SHOOTING-KIDS (Los Angeles) _ Six-year-old Joshua Stepakoff is
set to be released today from Childrens Hospital Los Angeles, where
he was treated for gunshot wounds he suffered in the North Valley
Jewish Community Center shooting. Benjamin Kadish, the 5-year-old
who was the most seriously wounded, is still in critical condition,
but is said to be improving. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the
``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
