California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-DNC (Los Angeles) _ The one-year countdown to the Democratic
National Convention coming to Los Angeles begins Saturday, and
officials said Friday they are on target in preparing to host the
three-day event leading to the nomination of the party's
presidential candidate. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CHIMP-NAME (Los Angeles) _ The contest to name the boy chimp at
the Los Angeles Zoo is in, um, full swing. Sample names already
submitted: Chimpy, Abu, Toko, Bongo, Bingo, Tropic, Max, Joey. The
promotion ends on Aug. 2 and zoo officials expect to have a name
chosen within two weeks after that. About 300 names have been
submitted so far. By Kathryn Combs. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-FAIRCHILD (Los Angeles) _ Wall Street gives an initial
endorsement to Walt Disney's decision to sell its Fairchild
Publication. The stock, which has been lagging on poor earnings for
the past year, bounces up 4 percent on hopes the parent company
will focus on studio and theme park divisions. By Dave McNary.
(Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
