million or more soared to a new record from April to June. The San
Francisco Bay area, benefiting from booming high-technology
companies, supplanted Beverly Hills as the state's leader in the
million-dollar market. By Greg Wilcox. (Will move in the ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
