the murder of a postal worker in Los Angeles. Yet despite lengthy
evaluations, Furrow was never ordered to remain under state
psychiatric care, and his case is another that raises questions
about whether states should tighten the laws on involuntary
commitment. By Timothy Egan. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in
``a'' news file.)
</P>
