   GAYS-MILITARY (Washington) _ The Pentagon announces its first
major revision of guidelines for its ``don't ask, don't tell''
policy on homosexuals in the military, including a new requirement
that commanders seek approval from senior officials at the Pentagon
before opening certain types of investigations of troops who admit
that they are gay. The revised guidelines, however, fail to satisfy
gay rights advocates. By Philip Shenon. (Scheduled to move by 8:30
p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 1,200 words.
</P>
