   INSIDE STORIES PROMOTED ON PAGE 1:
</P>
<P>
   NJ-MARTINI-DEATH (Hackensack, N.J.) _ After arguing for nearly
four years in New Jersey courts that his own execution should
procede, a convicted murderer has reversed himself and told his
lawyer to appeal his death sentence in federal court. The condemned
prisoner, John Martini, 69, changed his mind this week, about six
weeks before his scheduled execution by lethal injection. By Robert
Hanley. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
