<P>
   BEAN-BOOMERS (Freeport, Maine) _ First came the indoor trout
pond. Then there was the barnlike addition devoted to children's
clothes and accessories. Now comes what is perhaps the ultimate
sign that L.L. Bean, the 87-year-old arbiter of what's what in
rugged outerwear, is going after cosseted baby boomers in a big
way: The company's Maine hunting shoe, its first product and
essential icon, has been revamped. By Constance L. Hays.
</P>
