</P>
<P>
   ALUMINUM-ALCOA (Undated) _ Two days after Alcoa Inc., the
world's largest aluminum producer, offered to buy Reynolds Metals
Co. in a half-cash, half-stock deal valued at $5.8 billion, another
bidder, McCook Metals, has emerged with a higher, all-cash offer.
By Claudia H. Deutsch.
</P>
