<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   IOWA-STRAWPOLL (Des Moines, Iowa) _ Republican presidential
candidates kiss babies and eat barbecue in preparation for the Iowa
straw poll on Saturday while the apparent front-runner, Texas Gov.
George W. Bush, is campaigning elsewhere in the state. By BENNETT
ROTH and R.G. RATCLIFFE. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000-ANALYSIS (Undated) _ During her tenure as Texas
governor, Ann Richards once stood atop the state Capitol steps and
tried to make an outlandish joke to a group of reporters. One
reporter looked up at Richards. ``Are you serious, governor?'' She
replied, ``You people can just suck the humor right out of a
person.'' Gov. George W. Bush, the apparent front-runner for the
Republican presidential nomination, got a taste of what Richards
meant this week with the publication of interviews he granted to
Talk magazine. By R.G. RATCLIFFE. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   WHITE-HOUSE (Washington) _ We look at recent efforts by the
White House to use government events, executive pronouncements and
the president's pulpit to provide a backdrop for the campaign of
Vice President Gore and the Senate aspirations of First Lady
Hillary Rodham Clinton. By NANCY MATHIS. (Already filed.)
</P>
