   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   EL-CENIZO (El Cenizo, Texas) _ While most towns along the
U.S.-Mexico border are battling to keep illegal immigrants out,
this tiny locale on the outskirts of Laredo is embracing them. El
Cenizo recently passed two ordinances, one that makes it a ``safe
haven'' for illegals and another that makes Spanish the town's
official language. The action is troubling to federal officials and
has English-only advocates warning of the break-up of the United
States along lines of race and language. By THADDEUS HERRICK.
(Already filed.)
</P>
