<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TWO LINEMEN CHOOSE USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC has picked up oral commitments from defensive
lineman Jamaal Williams of St. Augustine High in San Diego and
offensive lineman Kenechi Udeze of Verbum Dei.
</P>
<P>
   Williams (6-foot-5, 250 pounds) has played just one year of
organized football. He attends the same school as former USC
defensive lineman Darrell Russell.
</P>
<P>
   Udeze (6-5, 310), who attended camps at USC and Michigan this
summer, was also being recruited by Iowa and Wisconsin.
</P>
<P>
   ``The upside potential is tremendous on both of these guys,''
said Rick Kimbrel, managing editor of PrepStar recruiting magazine.
</P>
<P>
   USC now has five oral commitments. Quarterback Matt Cassel of
Chatsworth, offensive lineman Joe McGuire of Servite and safety
Jason Leach of Bishop Amat had previously committed.
</P>
<P>
   No Steele: JC transfer linebacker Markus Steele of Long Beach
City College will not practice this weekend, because his summer
transcripts have not been processed and mailed to USC. Steele will
not practice before Monday, and it is possible he will not be
eligible until midweek.
</P>
<P>
   It looks as if wide receiver Craig Mitchell will be out until at
least midweek, because he needs two junior-college transcripts to
be processed.
</P>
<P>
   They are the only two players on the roster who are not in
Irvine for training camp.
</P>
<P>
   McCaffrey hurt: Starting left tackle Brent McCaffrey may not
practice for the first week, after puncturing his foot on a bed
frame.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've got an injury ... which is a little more significant
than we had thought,'' USC coach Paul Hackett said. ``We'll
probably be very cautious with him.''
</P>
<P>
   Freshman making impact: Hackett was pleased with the true
freshmen offensive linemen who had their first practices earlier
this week.
</P>
<P>
   ``Lucais MacKay has started working at the center position and
is very impressive,'' Hackett said. ``Probably the most impressive
of the bunch is Lenny Vandermade. The two tackles, Eric Torres and
Nate Steinbacher, are very impressive.''
</P>
<P>
   Davis ready: Defensive tackle Ennis Davis and running back
Malaefou MacKenzie will be limited to one practice per day to open
training camp. Both tore ligaments in their knees last season.
</P>
<P>
   Davis said he feels fine, although his quadriceps muscles are
not quite 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Soward passes: Wide receiver R. Jay Soward passed a running
endurance test Friday morning, after being forced to stop midway
through his first try Thursday, when his legs hurt.
</P>
<P>
   Practice dates: USC opens practice today at UC Irvine. The
Trojans will practice every day at Irvine until Aug. 27. Practice
sessions are scheduled at 9 a.m. and 3 p.m. Practices are open to
the public every day except Aug. 19, 21 and 24.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
